76561198018179096,Recommended,224940,30184154,Posted: 25 February,all,Macready,"""Here, Raziel. Every-thing is decided here. You cannot comprehend the magnitude, the rapture or the tragedy of this moment. And yet you must; if Nosgoth is to be dragged from the wreckage of it's damnation.""As stated elsewhere in these reviews, Soul Reaver 2 has the quality of story and voice acting that is God-tier.  It's epicness has been unrivavled, in my estimation, since it's inception several years ago. No story in video-games holds such weight that that of the Legacy of Kain series. This, imo, is the pinnacle of the story-telling in this series, from beginning to end. The twists and turns along with revelatory epiphonies that follow Raziel in his quest for the Truth are in no way, in any sense of the imagination, trivial.History and time-travel also make their appearance here in a way that you've likely not fathomed possible, given the ""Back to the Future"" esque sense of time-travel most of modern media is inundated with. History, in particular, is a character in the story that can and will take action in the need to preserve continuity, a stunning inclusion and narrative-defining element. I'll not spoil the details here but the rules this universe are bound by are unique and very concievable, lending credence to the overal arc of this tale.The voice acting is a remarkable feat in this game. Most games have solitary actors being cued up for their lines, leaving much to be desired in the natural ebb and flow of a genuine conversation; often stilted and jarring given that actors simply have to pretend they are talking with someone else when giving their lines. Not here. Every scene of dialogue has actors standing side-by-side in a sound booth, bouncing line after line off one another in such a way you would beleive these characters to be rea not only in their solidity but also in their convictions. Truly an example of a byegone era of voice acting. Unparralleled. A treat to be savored, for sure.If you've never experienced the joy of Soul Reaver, I would implore you to either buy the game and play it (though the combat and platforming are a little dated by todays standards, the puzzles are fun though) or watch the movies of them online, starting with either the first soul reaver or the first legacy of Kain entry. It's hard to wrap your head around at first because there is much context to the story but once you get to this entry you are simply hooked.There's nothing like this entry in all of the video games that I've ever played. Do yourself a favor and sink your teeth into it. You won't be disappointed"
