,Recommended,224940,12698361,"Posted: 30 October, 2014",all,Artibius,"PROS:+ awesome story+ cool game soundtrack+ great voice acting+ enhanced controls and graphics (compared to SR1)+ two realms - physical and spectral+ puzzlesCONS:- weaker boss fights- simpler gameplay (compared to SR1)- another open ending hinting to LoK: Defiance- can have compatibility problems on some PCsComment:Soul Reaver 2 is a sequel to one of my favourite games of all time so of course I had to play it as well. And overall this is a good game that combines combat and puzzles in the various time periods of Nosgoth. This time around the game is less difficult but still keeps it's challenge. The game keeps the mechanic of shifting between physical and spectral realm. Although the return to the physical realm is a bit changed. So if you die in the physical world you shift to the spectral one. There is a rather visible lack of good/epic boss fights in this sequel and while it does make sense story-wise I have to say it takes away from the gameplay a bit. The story and narrative, reasons why I love this series, remain superb. The story telling is enhanced by (slightly) better graphics, the writing and voice acting are great as always. I like the soundtrack too. The downsides are that the game is old so graphics and compatibility are really lacking (though it is a lot better than SR1), however it runs fine on my Win7 laptop. The ending is reather open again and that can get annoying in this series, though it does finally finish in LoK: Defiance. I really like the Soul Reaver series and as such I have to recommend this one as well, not just because I like it but also because it is a good game worth trying out.------------------------------------------------------------------If you liked this review you can find more on theCurator pageor in myReview Corner."
