,Not Recommended,224940,34132334,Posted: 9 August,all,torunar,"Being a huge fan of the first Soul Reaver game and the whole Legacy of Kain series I have mixed feelings about this title.The game has a lot of pros:- The story is awesome. It seamlessly continues the previous game and fills the gaps of the Blood Omen storyline.- The cinematics and the cutscenes are well directed and spectacular.- The voice acting is awesome.- The character design is brilliant.However, this game is awfully broken in many aspects:- It has good cutscenes, but it also has too much unskippable cutscenes that will interrupt you every 20-30 minutes of the gameplay.- Platforming and 3rd person camera are as bad as they were in Soul Reaver 1. This, and a ton of swimming sections can be infuriating.- Battles are frustrating: the challenge is achieved by making enemies enormous damage sponges. Moreover, they are simply annoying: most of the time enemies will flee from you / block you / charge-stun you. There are a lot of battles but you will feel the urge to avoid them. Oh, and the enemies are tend to re-spawn just behind your back.- Environments are dull, long and boring corridors. No exploration and no secrets. Not being such a big deal story-wise, they were the things that made the first Soul Reaver and the original Blood Omen one of the most exciting games.- The backtracking in this game has no meaning at all, but its amount is just brutal.- Yay, block-pushing puzzles from the first game are gone! Nay, mirror-rotating-and-pushing puzzles took their place...tl;dr: Will recommend only to die-hard fans of Legacy of Kain franchise.For others: just read the plot in some wiki and move on to the next game in the series."
