,Recommended,224940,33772267,Posted: 24 July,all,Doctor Soul,"A very appreciated Gem of the 2000s Gaming Age. Now don't go in thinking that it has alot to offer like collectibles or anything extra. This is a textbook ""Linear"" game that is all about it's story and a damn good one.Soul Reaver 2 picks back up on the journey of Raziel, Kain's former top vampire lieutenant who had been condemned to a painful demise and reborn as a soul devouring phantasm. Unbound by the will of his master, Raziel had embarked on a quest of redemption and vengeance throughout Nosgoth, now rendered into an inhospitable wasteland due to Kain's selfish and parasitic ambitions. Hunting down his vampire brethren and claiming their corrupted souls, Raziel confronts Kain within the Chronoplast, a chamber built by Moebius The Timestreamer.Armed with nothing left but rage and his Wraith Blade, Raziel chases after Kain through one of The Chronoplast's portals, hurled through time into one of Nosgoth's earlier centuries of history and greeted by the TimeStreamer himself, Moebius.-However, While the game and it's story are incredible to play, this PC/Steam port version of the game is anything but stable unless you have a good card or program to run it.-Opening FMV will run black and voices sped up- Game will freeze within minutes and not respond-Raziel's Shift between the Spectral and Material realms won't function properly, which can be bad with certain puzzles needed for progression.-Swimming is very buggy as you constantly bounce up and downThere are discussions to get pass this, and if you do, then I recommend this game for anyone looking for a great story and a simple good game worth finishing."
