,Recommended,224940,34377926,Posted: 20 August,all,AkiSmash,"I see reviews saying this is unplayable on Windows 10. Have no fear, because it actually does. For me at least, with no issues.This is a game I grew up with, with superb storytelling and voice acting despite its combat. Sadly none of my Xbox controllers worked for this, but apparently will work wonders with a PS4 controller. Only thing of course it that it will still name your buttons numbers rather than the symbol. It's common, and takes a bit to get used to. You also may have to mess around with the button mappings, cause jump was L1 at first- this game is picking favorites. There is also no widescreen option, but it's not a big issue for me. If it bothers you, there is a mod for it.I heavily recommend this game, and the Legacy of Kain series as a whole. Don't miss out on an amazingly long and interesting story.and ""how do i solve this puzzle"" will be repeated over and over"
